===Etymology===
from Greek {{polytonic|[[Καδμεία]]}} ([[calamine]]), a Cadmium-bearing mixture of minerals, which was named after the god, {{polytonic|[[Κάδμος]]}} ([[Cadmus]])

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
{{wikipedia}}

# a metallic chemical element (''symbol'' Cd) with an [[atomic number]] of 48.

